deck: After the events of Second Coming and the stunning conclusion to X-Force, X-23 strikes out on her own in this all-new ongoing series, written by best-selling author MARJORIE LIU, spinning out of the events of Wolverine #1! X-23 has never had an easy relationship with the rest of the X-Men, but when she learns someone has taken down Wolverine, she must step up to fill his shoes.
description:
To discover her true self, X-23 has decided to leave Utopia on a personal mission. Accompanied by Remy Lebeau, she sets out on an adventure that takes her to the American Southwest and some old enemies. It also takes her to the island of Madripoor in search of the Weapon X program. Once she arrives, she discovers a city under siege and being controlled by none other than Wolverine's son, Daken.

Collected Editions

  • X-23: The Killing Dream (#1-6)
  • X-23: The Complete Collection Volume 1 (#1-3)
  • X-23: The Complete Collection Volume 2 (#4-21)
  • Daken/X-23: Collision (Daken: Dark Wolverine #5-9, X-23 #7-9)
  • X-23: Chaos Theory (#10-16)

  • X-23: Misadventures in Babysitting (#17-20, 22)
name: X-23
